docs.abstract: With her first museum retrospective, the artist (and fashion muse) talks about confecting fanciful works with a core of steel.
docs.snippet: With her first museum retrospective, the artist (and fashion muse) talks about confecting fanciful works with a core of steel.
docs.lead_paragraph: If Rachel Feinstein had a spirit guide, it would probably be Sleeping Beauty. For the artist — known for her extravagantly detailed fantasy sculptures, installations and paintings — the fairy tale princess may be the most relatable of the otherworldly creatures that animate her work.

headline.main: Rachel Feinstein Unveils the Darker Side of Fantasyland

docs.abstract: Mr. Castro, the former housing secretary and mayor of San Antonio, was the only Latino candidate in the race. He championed progressive policies but did not find his footing in polls.
docs.snippet: Mr. Castro, the former housing secretary and mayor of San Antonio, was the only Latino candidate in the race. He championed progressive policies but did not find his footing in polls.
docs.lead_paragraph: Julián Castro, the former housing secretary who was the only Latino candidate in the Democratic primary, said Thursday he would end his bid for the presidency, capping a yearlong campaign where he struggled in polls but remained a policy pacesetter on immigration and fighting poverty.

headline.main: Julián Castro Ends Presidential Run: ‘It Simply Isn’t Our Time’
headline.print_headline: Castro Ends Campaign for President, Saying It ‘Simply Isn’t Our Time’
